unwound.title: Hundreds wait to vote in Georgia after voting machines break down at Gwinnett County polling place
unwound.description: Hundreds of voters are reportedly waiting to vote at one Georgia polling place due to a technical issue with voting machines. The Atlanta Journal Constitution reported that election officials in Gwinnett County have confirmed that the machines are down at Anderson-Livsey Elementary School. “The line of hundreds of waiting voters stretched the entire length of the school,” the paper noted. Gwinnett County spokesman Joe Sorenson said that new machines would have to be brought in. […]
